# Memodee — Project Rules

## Linear workflow
When implementing a Linear issue:
1. Read the issue via the Linear MCP before writing any code
2. Search the codebase to locate exact files before making changes
3. Run tests and build before finishing (npm run test && npm run build)
4. Flag pre-existing issues you encountered but did not change — don't fix them
5. Show me the result or before/after so I can verify visually before closing

## Project context
- Product name: Memodee (marketed as "ChatGPT Archive")
- Client-side app — core features run entirely in the browser via IndexedDB (Dexie)
- No backend except a lightweight Express server for the Notion proxy (/api/notion-proxy)
- Framework: Vite + React + TypeScript (not Next.js)
- Key libs: Zustand (state), Dexie (IndexedDB), Fuse.js (fuzzy search), Recharts (charts), Sonner (toasts), React Router, TanStack Virtual

## Key entry points
- src/main.tsx, src/App.tsx
- src/components/layout/AppShell.tsx
- src/pages/* (Import, Library, Analytics, Settings)
- src/store/* (Zustand stores)
- src/lib/* (db.ts, parser.ts, etc.)

## Constraints
- Never add a backend feature that could be done client-side
- Never persist user data to a server — everything stays in IndexedDB
- Don't touch the Notion proxy unless the task explicitly involves it